Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_bump_cluster(25.10)                          create_bump_cluster(25.10)

Name
       create_bump_cluster - Creates bump clusters according to region, layer,
       pitch, and size

Syntax
       create_bump_cluster

       [-help]

       [-area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}]

       [-enclosure {<a b>}]

       -layer <name>

       -pitch {<x y>}

       -size {<n m>}

       [[-type {signal | power | ground}] | [-nets {<net>+}]]

       Creates  bump  clusters  according  to  region, layer, pitch, and size.
       fcroute can be used to route bump clusters and connect to  IO  pads  or
       probing pads. Both signal and PG nets are supported. The routing layers
       are  specified using the fcroute -layerChangeBotLayer and -layerChange-
       TopLayer parameters.

       The created clusters are defined by a special wire with a single pin in
       the bump layer and have subclass names (bump_cluster_%d).  The  cluster
       is a rectangular metal on the bump layer.

       The tool returns an error in the following scenarios:

              * The created bump cluster can cause DRCs:

                Fail to create bump_cluster_"%d" as DRC exists.

              * A different bump cell exists in the area of the bump cluster:

                Fail to create bump clusters as inconsistent bump cell.

       You need to check bump clusters before routing. You can:

              * Delete a cluster using editDelete -subclass:

                editDelete -subclass {<cluster_name>}

                This  deletes  clusters with the specified name. Wildcards can
                be used in cluster_name.

              * Select a cluster using editSelect -subclass.

                editSelect -subclass {<cluster_name>}

                This selects clusters with the specified name.  Wildcards  can
                be used in cluster_name.

       You can also delete or select clusters using the GUI.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each create_bump_cluster parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man create_bump_cluster

       -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Limits the area from which bumps need to be  grouped  into  bump
              clusters.  The tool creates bump clusters from left to right and
              bottom to top in this region.

              By default, the entire floorplan area is used for grouping bumps
              into clusters.

              Data_type: box, optional

       -enclosure {<a b>}
              Specifies that the distance from  the  bump-array  edge  to  the
              cluster-metal edge is a in the x direction and b in the y direc-
              tion.

              a and b are unified in all bump cluster groups.

              Data_type: point, optional

       -layer <name>
              Specifies  the  metal layer of the cluster. The default layer is
              the bump layer.

              Data_type: string, required

       -nets {<net>+}
              Specifies the nets of the bumps to be included in clusters. Only
              bumps with the same net can be grouped together in a  particular
              cluster.  The type of the cluster net can be specified using the
              -type parameter. If -type and -nets are not specified, all  sig-
              nal and PG nets are considered as bump cluster nets.

              Data_type: (net)+, optional

       -pitch {<x y>}
              Specifies the <x> pitch and <y> pitch for the bumps in the clus-
              ter.  Only bumps with the specified bump pitch can be grouped in
              bump clusters.

              Data_type: point, required

       -size {<n m>}
              Specifies the <n*m> size of clusters. There are n*m bumps in one
              cluster.

              Data_type: string, required

       -type {signal power ground}
              Specifies the type of the bump cluster net. If -type  and  -nets
              are not specified, all signal and PG nets are considered as bump
              cluster nets.

              Data_type: enum, optional

Examples
              *

                The  following  command creates 3x4-sized bump clusters in the
                specified region:

                create_bump_cluster -area {0 0 80 100} -pitch {3 2} -enclosure
                {1.5 1} -size {3 4}

                The expected result is as shown below:

                Notes

                * The bumps on the top left of the specified area have a  dif-
                  ferent  pitch  so are not included in the bump clusters cre-
                  ated by this command.

                * Both the bump clusters in red-dash squares are  not  created
                  to prevent DRC issues.

              * The following set of commands route the bump clusters:

                setFlipChipMode -route_bump_cluster true

                fcroute  -type  signal -layerChangeBotLayer AP -layerChangeTo-
                pLayer AP

Related Information
